name: East San Gabriel Valley Coalition
review_text: They didn't want to help me, they said you have to have a car to receive help. And 211 info it's says it's a walk in I have proof and I even showed it. And they still didn't help me.   Hopefully they don't turn nobody else away because they walked or came on the bus. The program is part of the church wow. Turning me away when all I did was ask for help when that is their duty. The lady's I spoke to said if someone complains they could get shut down. Change your ways with your help or you might get shut down for good.

name: East San Gabriel Valley Coalition
review_text: I got denied for going on my bike, my motorized bike(needs gas Like a car),walking and all because I ddnt show up in a car as it is im homeless already...They said the city or neighbord complain but i called the city of La Puente and Asked about the walk up policy and they said they have no idea what im talking about...ive gone on my motorized bike before and they actually gave me stuff but this time i got denied...then they told to go look for help somewhere else or to call someother place...no snacks no water no hygiene kit nothing at all...theres no point in helping if you cant help everybody regardless if they have a car or not ....

name: East San Gabriel Valley Coalition
review_text: This morning, I endeavored to assist a homeless man on the street, shivering in the cold rain. After supplying him with a change of clothes, a jacket, a tent, food, and coffee, I attempted to contact several shelters, only to be disappointed as most of them did not answer. Eventually, I connected with a kind lady who guided me to a shelter where I could safely drop off the homeless man to stay dry throughout the week of rain. I want to express my gratitude for her assistance and say thank you.

name: East San Gabriel Valley Coalition
review_text: My husband and I went out there after calling them and were told on the phone that they could put us up at a motel for a month. When we arrived there, we were told that in order for them to help us, we would have to give them the total move in cost for them to hold until our place was ready for us to move into. We told them that we would not have any money until the 3rd of July and they said that they would make arrangements for us to stay at the motel for a month as long as we gave them 1500 dollars to hold until our place was ready to move into. Then about 3 days into our stay,they called and wanted us to bring them confirmation that we were actually going to move into the trailer that we were trying to rent. There was no way that we were going to be able to get that until the work on the trailer was complete. This organization claims to be concerned about the homeless people, but they are not concerned at all. They obviously have never been in the position of being without a place to live or else they would not make demands that a person who is homeless cannot possibly meet. I would recommend that any homeless person looking for any help, to stay away from this organization because they don't really care even though they say that they do.

review_text: Hi well my mother and i have been homeless going on almost three years  I've never been thru any of this in my life time . my mother and me have always had a place to live it Was my mom who told me about this church the staff that works there they welcome every one with open arms and a smile to go with it they don't look down on us who are having a hard time at the moment they offer us shower's Mon thru Thursday morning only they give us 3 warm meals a day. name: East San Gabriel Valley Coalition
review_text:
I just spoke with one of the women in the office. I answered the question of how I just became homeless. She assumed I said I'm disabled when I told her my former employer who is expecting me out of his house thinks I'm disabled and don't know how to do anything like cleaning.

When someone calls asking for assistance, even if it's a motel room, never tell them to stay and make it work with someone who clearly wants the person out!

name: East San Gabriel Valley Coalition
review_text: Every year my  husband and I donate to a charity instead of giving each other  Christmas gifts, this year it was to the ESGVC  for the homeless.  They have a very good article on what is needed.   It was a little hard to find as I got off the freeway on 7th Ave  left on Palm,  Palm then goes into ALPERN  and it was on the right side  .   I totally missed it as I was looking for Turnbull Canyon Road.  After asking someone It was easy to find.    I took a car load of NEW ITEMS  warm clothing for men and women,  was told they needed socks  so I purchased bags of socks ,  I was told that they needed stuff to take a shower , Razors  shaving cream, deodorant ,  Tooth brushes and paste, I also purchased sanitay pads for the women and lotion , and other bathroom items  lots of  antibacterial wipes .  Its amazing how much bathroom items you can purchase for $100  at the .99 cent store. .  A friend who's husband travels  a lot for work gave me a huge bag of all the items the hotels give  you.  I felt like Santa with all my goodies.. I hope I put a smile on someones face when they  get a shower, put on a clean  new shirt,  new socks.. We take for granted these everyday  .  Help the homeless.  And renew your Soul.
